noun.description: The direction towards the point of the horizon midway between south and east, or the point on the horizon itself.
examples: a ship was coming in from the south-east

noun.description: The south-eastern part of a country, region, or town.
examples: opposition to Turkish influence was strongest in the south-east

adjective.description: Lying towards, near, or facing the south-east.
examples: a table stood in the south-east corner

adjective.description: Of or denoting the south-eastern part of a specified country, region, or town or its inhabitants.

examples: turn south-east to return to your starting point
